        public java.lang.String response(java.lang.String projectName,
                                 int status,
                                 java.lang.String message,
                                 int timeout,
                                 java.lang.String icon,
                                 java.lang.String colour)
        Construct a response with all values manually set.
        Parameters:
        projectName - The name of the CurseForge project.
        status - The statuscode. Status 0: Already exists. Status 1: OK, generating. Status 2: Error occurred.
        message - The message the requester should care about.
        timeout - Timeout in milliseconds after which the notification in our Quasar frontend should disappear.
        icon - The icon to be displayed in the notification.
        colour - The colour of the notification.
        Returns:
        String. Returns the aforementioned parameters wrapped in JSON.

      • response

        public java.lang.String response(int projectID,
                                 int status,
                                 java.lang.String message,
                                 int timeout,
                                 java.lang.String icon,

        Construct a response with values acquired from the CurseForge API.
        Parameters:
        projectID - The id with which to gather the name of the project.
        status - The statuscode. Status 0: Already exists. Status 1: OK, generating. Status 2: Error occurred.
        message - The message the requester should care about.
        timeout - Timeout in milliseconds after which the notification in our Quasar frontend should disappear.
        icon - The icon to be displayed in the notification.
        colour - The colour of the notification.
        Returns:
        String. Returns the aforementioned parameters wrapped in JSON.
